description: Do not use the void operator on expressions
globs: **/*.{ts,mjs,vue}
alwaysApply: false
---

# No `void` operator

Do not prefix expressions with the `void` operator to ignore promises or return values. Call the function or chain `.catch()` directly.

```typescript
// Good
askLlmToIdentifyInterests(userPrompt, assistantResponse, source).catch((error) => {
  logTurnError('interests identification failed', error, { source });
});

maybeCreateResponseImpl();
checkSchedules();

// Bad
void askLlmToIdentifyInterests(...).catch(handleError);
void maybeCreateResponseImpl();
void checkSchedules();
```

`void` in **type positions** is fine (`() => void`, `Promise<void>`). This rule is only for the `void` **operator** on expressions.
